body:
AccountsListFragment didn't save it state that caused to displaying identical fragments in ViewPager.

Steps to reproduce:
- open homescreen (AccountsActivity);
- check ViewPager fragments;
- rotate device;
- check ViewPager fragments, they all will have mDisplayMode with value TOP_LEVEL.

![device-2016-04-11-231446](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1074496/14442662/aa01946c-0043-11e6-9b74-869293a5cad4.png)

**How to reproduce**
1. Open a new xml file from GnuCash for Android (GCA);
2. Enter some transaction;
3. Select Export from GCA and the suggested time may be wrong (the difference seems to be exactly your time zone):
![2016-01-11 18 12 10](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5398143/12242408/11ed2520-b880-11e5-851d-6f25d281c0f7.png)

**Additional information**
- If we select export again, the suggested time seems to be correct;
- I've installed GCA 2.0.5 on my Nexus 5 running Android 6.0.1.

Importing old backups which do not have balanced splits fails due to a "FOREIGN key constraint fails" when bulk adding splits. This I think is the the split account uid foreign constraint.
Auto-balancing takes place during the import process (and that includes creating the imbalance account). So db has to be cleared before importing starts. I've made the adjustments in the develop branch, but still the import fails.
@fefe982 could you look into it? I could send you some old files if you don't have any.

Some transactions may be saved with a timestamp in the future. These should be ignored when computing the account balance. The transaction timestamp is set by the user.

There are always the created_at and modified_at timestamps in the db (develop) which we can lookup for other purposes. 

@fefe982 could you look into this? Thanks

